Blitz DFIR is an original evidence-safety, orchestration, audit, and reporting
layer for DFIR workflows. It does not bundle raw forensic tools, commercial
agent runtimes, SANS SIFT Workstation, Protocol SIFT, Claude Code, OpenClaw,
Ollama, or forensic evidence datasets.

Third-party dependency and external-tool license information is maintained in:

    THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md

Names such as SANS, SIFT Workstation, Protocol SIFT, Claude Code, OpenClaw,
Ollama, Volatility, Plaso/log2timeline, Wireshark, YARA, The Sleuth Kit, and
Chainsaw are the property of their respective owners. Reference to those names
does not imply endorsement, sponsorship, affiliation, or redistribution.

Protocol SIFT is referenced as an external, optional workflow/integration path.
Blitz DFIR does not include Protocol SIFT files or modify Protocol SIFT. If a
future package copies or redistributes Protocol SIFT material, confirm and
comply with the upstream license or obtain permission first.
